title: borden
body:
Borden, Inc., was an American producer of food and beverage products, consumer products, and industrial products. At one time, the company was the largest U.S. producer of dairy and pasta products. Its food division, Borden Foods, was based in Columbus, Ohio, and focused primarily on pasta and pasta sauces, bakery products, snacks, processed cheese, jams and jellies, and ice cream. It was best known for its Borden Ice Cream, Meadow Gold milk, Creamette pasta, and Borden Condensed Milk brands. Its consumer products and industrial segment marketed wallpaper, adhesives, plastics and resins. By 1993, sales of food products accounted for 67 percent of its revenues. It was also known for its Elmer's Glue and Krazy Glue.

After significant financial losses in the early 1990s and a leveraged buyout by KKR in 1995, Borden divested itself of its various divisions, brands and businesses. KKR shuttered Borden's food products operations in 2001, and divested all its other Borden operations in 2005. The Borden dairy brands are currently used by both Dean Foods and Grupo Lala (as Borden Milk Products) for milk and by Dairy Farmers of America for cheese.

title: riderman
body:
Enemy, and later ally, of [[kamen_rider_v3|Kamen Rider V3]]. Also known as the "Avenging Demon".

A former scientist of the Destron organization framed as a traitor, Jouji Yuki takes up the name of Riderman to eliminate V3 and clear his name.

Riderman is not named the 4th Kamen Rider until [spoiler]he sacrifices himself to redirect a missile bound for Tokyo.[/spoiler]

His distinguishing features include his mechanical right arm and helmet that exposes the lower half of his face.

title: kamen_rider_x
body:
The fifth [[Kamen Rider]] and the protagonist of the franchise's third television series. Sometimes referred to as "X Rider."

After an attack on his father's laboratory orchestrated by the Government of Darkness, Keisuke Jin is surgically altered into Kamen Rider X and begins his campaign to end the organization's ambitions.

X is colored white with a red chest plate and accents. His design is based on a giant water bug, and thus is capable of operating underwater.

title: kamen_rider_v3
body:
Protagonist of the second television series in the [[Kamen Rider]] franchise.

To avenge his slain family, Shirou Kazami asks Kamen Riders [[kamen_rider_1|No. 1]] and [[kamen_rider_2|No. 2]]  to alter him into a cyborg. Though reluctant at first, the Riders grant his request. With a worthy successor, the Riders depart, leaving Kamen Rider V3 to defend Japan and bring down the organization responsible for his family's murder, Destron.

V3 is distinguished by his red helmet with green compound eyes, white scarf, and green body suit. He is modeled after a dragonfly.

title: kamen_rider_hibiki
body:
Lead Rider of [[kamen_rider_hibiki_(series)|Kamen Rider Hibiki]], fifteenth show of the Kamen Rider series and sixth of the Heisei generation.

Hibiki is a veteran Oni Rider, having given up his humanity and his old name - Hidaka Hitoshi - to fight the Makamou, human-eating monsters who can only be defeated with the power of pure sound. When not fighting, Hibiki takes on his form when he was still Hitoshi.

Hibiki fights using [i]bachi[/i] sticks, which were used for [i]taiko[/i] drums. He can also upgrade into Hibiki Kurenai and finally Armed Hibiki.

title: kamen_rider_super-1
body:
The title [[Kamen Rider]] of the franchise's 7th installment.

Kazuya Oki aspires of going into outer space. To achieve his dream, he volunteers to undergo surgery to be made into an astronaut that can survive in space without the need of bulky space suits. The operation is a success and he is codenamed "Super-1".

The Dogma Kingdom attacks the launch base before Oki is sent up into space, leaving him as the sole survivor. Bent on avenging his colleagues, he returns to Japan to begin training that allows him to transform into Kamen Rider Super-1.

Super-1 is primarily colored silver and black, with a red scarf. His design is based on a hornet.
other_names: 仮面ライダースーパー1

title: kamen_rider_stronger
body:
Hero of the fifth [[Kamen Rider]] series.

Shigeru Jou volunteers to be made into one of Black Satan's cyborg soldiers, suspicious of their involvement in his friend's murder. With the operation complete, he escapes their headquarters taking a fellow altered human with him, [[electro_wave_human_tackle|Tackle]]. Together, they begin their campaign against evil.

Stronger has large green compound eyes and the letter "S" emblazoned on his chest. His design is based on the Japanese rhinoceros beetle.
other_names: 仮面ライダーストロンガー

title: kamen_rider_blade
body:
Lead Rider of [[kamen_rider_blade_(series)|Kamen Rider Blade]], fourteenth show of the Kamen Rider series and fifth of the Heisei generation.

Kenzaki Kazuma is an orphan whose zeal to protect the defenseless earned him a place in BOARD, a clandestine organization fighting the Undead, monsters who represent species vying for supreme reign over the world. Kenzaki was given the Rider System-02 - Blade - to help him fight off the Undead menace.

Blade has an indigo color scheme, and is patterned after the Hercules beetle ([i]dynastes hercules[/i]) and the Spades suit. He also has access to the winged Jack Form, as well as the powerful King Form.
other_names: 仮面ライダーブレイド

title: kamen_rider_amazon
body:
The sole protagonist of the fourth television series in the [[Kamen Rider]] franchise.

Adopted by a local tribe after surviving a plane crash in the Amazon rainforest, he returns to Japan to take back a sacred armlet that had been stolen from his village.

A departure from his cyborg predecessors, Amazon resembles a combination of a giant lizard and possibly a piranha (people are still not sure). Despite his unique look, he still retains the traditional [[scarf]] and [[compound eyes]] of a Kamen Rider.
other_names: 仮面ライダーアマゾン

title: waltrud_krupinski
body:
Waltrud Krupinski (ヴァルトルート・クルピンスキー) is a veteran ace of the [[502nd Joint Fighter Wing]], originating from [[Karlsland]]. Her familiar is the Weimaraner.

Considered Karlsland's top veteran Ace, she joined the JG52 at around the same time as [[Gertrud Barkhorn]] and [[Erica Hartmann]], whom she considers good friends. She spent a good deal of time with Erica as her lead wingman. Among the 502nd JFW base, only Flight Lieutenant [[Gundula Rall]] has a higher confirmed kill count.

Tall, slender, and elegant, she has earned the nickname "Countess". She is also a hard-drinking womanizer and a hedonist with an easygoing personality. Despite her dauntless dog-fighting skill and sure marksmanship, her tendency to discard personal safety in favor of lining up for the attack rather than waiting means that she damages an unusually large number of Striker Unit, often making emergency landings under enemy fire.

Waltrud is based off Prussian-born German ace "Walter Krupinski":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walter_Krupinski who, similar to Waltrud, was nicknamed Graf Pinski (Count Pinski) due to his Prussian origins.
other_names: ヴァルトルート・クルピンスキー

title: ikusa_megami_(series)
body:
Known in english as Battle Goddess, or War Goddess, Ikusa Megami is a series of adult video games developed by "Eushully":http://www.eukleia.co.jp/eushully/main.html that follow the exploits of [[Celica_Sylphil|Celica Sylphil (Serika)]], a wandering fighter with the body of a goddess through the magical kingdom of Rewinia.

Games in the series:
1999: [[ikusa_megami|Ikusa Megami]], first game in the series.
2002: [[ikusa_megami_ii|Ikusa Megami 2 ~Ushinawareshi Kioku e no Chinkonka~]], direct sequel to the first game.
2008: [[ikusa_megami_zero|Ikusa Megami Zero]], prequel to the events of the entire series.
2010: [[ikusa_megami_verita|Ikusa Megami VERITA]], sequel to [[genrin_no_kishougun_2|Princess General 2]] and prequel to the first [[ikusa_megami|Battle Goddess]]
2014: [[tenbin_no_la_dea_~ikusa_megami_memoria~|Tenbin no La DEA. ~Ikusa Megami MEMORIA~]], a remake of the original [[ikusa_megami|Battle Goddess]], taking its place in the canon.

title: kamen_rider_faiz
body:
Lead Rider of [[Kamen Rider 555]], thirteenth show of the Kamen Rider series and fourth of the Heisei generation.

Inui Takumi is a lone wolf who was made the reluctant protector of a suitcase containing the Faiz Gear, using its contents to become Faiz and eliminate Orphnochs, monsters who feed on humans and are said to be humanity's next evolutionary step.

Faiz has a black color scheme with red "photon blood" vessels running across the suit. His design is inspired by the firefly and the Greek letter Φ.

He can change into two advanced forms: the speed-oriented Accel Form and the power-oriented Blaster Form.
other_names: 仮面ライダーファイズ

title: kamen_rider_ryuki
body:
Lead Rider of [[kamen_rider_ryuki_(series)|Kamen Rider Ryuki]], twelfth show of the Kamen Rider series and third of the Heisei generation, as well as the first Rider from the same generation to be given an American adaptation, [i]Dragon Knight[/i].

Rookie journalist Kidou Shinji finds himself in the middle of the Rider War, a deathmatch between 13 Kamen Riders, upon making a contract with [[Dragreder]], a Mirror Monster (themselves responsible for mysterious deaths throughout the city), to transform into Ryuki, fighting both Mirror Monsters and other Riders, as well as uncovering the truth of the Rider War.

Ryuki has a red color scheme and is modeled after both the Chinese dragon and a knight. He also uses Advent Cards to enhance his combat capabilities. Finally, he can upgrade into the bulkier, more powerful Ryuki Survive Form.

Yamabiko: A yamabiko (山彦, 幽谷響) is a sprite/youkai/god known in the Japanese folklore. In modern Japanese, yamabiko (やまびこ, 山彦 ["幽谷響" can't be used here]) is a word that refers to the phenomenon of the "reflection of sounds in mountains or valleys". In the old days of Japan, people thought echoes occurred because a yamabiko living in the mountains replied back or manipulated the sound.

title: tsunemori_akane
body: [b]Tsunemori Akane (常守 朱)[/b] is the main female character of [[Psycho-Pass]]. A young and idealist girl and a brilliant student, Tsunemori opted to join the Public Safety Bureau because she believed that she could make a difference. While very inexperienced and not used to the criminal world, she is shown to have a very strong mind, being able to shrug off the trauma of terrible events relatively easily. She has a strong sense of justice which sometimes doesn't agree with Sybil's decisions, and is generally very courageous. She is also very polite and is easily embarrassed. After the events of the first episode she and Kougami form a bond and she deeply cares for him. Tsunemori is also a pacifist, and has not fired a lethal shot at anyone. In episode 11 [spoiler]Makishima killed her friend Yuki, after which she became determined to catch him. In episode 16 she saves Kougami from being killed by Makishima and narrowly stops herself from killing him in revenge for Yuki.[/spoiler]

title: tachibana_wataru
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Thirteen-year-old fiance of [[Sanzen'in Nagi]], despite neither having feelings for each other - instead, Wataru has a crush on Nagi's best friend [[Saginomiya Isumi]]. He lives in and runs a video-rental store - the last remnant of his family's once vast business enterprise - with his maid [[Kijima Saki]].

title: segawa_izumi
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Class Representative for [[Ayasaki Hayate]]'s class and part of a trio of proud school underachievers, together with classmates [[Asakaze Risa]] and [[Hanabishi Miki]], who hang around with [[Katsura Yukiji]]. Izumi is the daughter of the president of a large manufacturing company, and is frequently the butt of pranks from Risa and Miki. She's also the girl closest to Hayate among the trio.

title: nishizawa_ayumu
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

[[Ayasaki Hayate]]'s old schoolmate prior to becoming [[Sanzen'in Nagi]]'s butler, who harbors a crush on him, to the point that she'd lash out at anyone who speaks ill of him. She is also good friends with [[Katsura Hinagiku]], who also has a crush on Hayate. The anime adaptation frequently made fun of her rather large appetite.

title: klaus_seishirou
body:

title: kijima_saki
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Twenty-year-old maid of [[Tachibana Wataru]], who helps him run a video-rental store - the last of the Tachibanas' once prosperous business enterprise. She is very protective of Wataru, even fearing he will start watching porn upon reaching puberty, but greatly fears being touched anywhere by other males, such as [[Ayasaki Hayate]].

title: katsura_yukiji
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

[[katsura_hinagiku|Hinagiku]]'s 28-year-old elder sister and history teacher (and also gate guard) at Hakuou Academy. Compared to her orderly younger sister, Yukiji is rather childish, irresponsible and also an alcoholic. She frequently hangs around with a trio of underachieving students - [[Asakaze Risa]], [[Segawa Izumi]] and [[Hanabishi Miki]].

title: katsura_hinagiku
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Student Council President of Hakuou Academy, where [[Ayasaki Hayate]], [[Sanzen'in Nagi]] and [[Saginomiya Isumi]] attend, as well as younger sister of [[katsura_yukiji|Yukiji]], one of the school's teachers. Intelligent, well-mannered (in contrast to her alcoholic older sister) and popular with the girls, Hina, as she is known, is also skilled at kendo. After being saved by Hayate from being stuck on a tree (due to her agoraphobia), she has developed feelings for him.

title: hanabishi_miki
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

A member of Hakuou Academy's Student Council, Class Vice-Representative to [[Ayasaki Hayate]]'s class, and part of a trio of proud school underachievers together with [[Asakaze Risa]] and [[Segawa Izumi]], who hang around with [[Katsura Yukiji]]. As the daughter of a government official and granddaughter of a former Prime Minister, Miki is rather inquisitive, and enjoys causing trouble to Student Council President [[Katsura Hinagiku]], all the while harboring a crush on her.

title: asakaze_risa
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

Head of Hakuou Academy's Disciplinary Committee and part of a trio of proud school underachievers, along with [[Segawa Izumi]] and [[Hanabishi Miki]], who hang around with [[Katsura Yukiji]]. Her family lives in a Shinto shrine, and, in stark contrast to her duty, likes to cause trouble with her tomboyish attitude and penchant for mischief.

title: aizawa_sakuya
body:
A supporting character from [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

[[Sanzen'in Nagi]]'s cousin from Kansai and an aspiring manzai stand-up comedian. While as rich and loud as her cousin, Sakuya is also caring, having taken care of Nagi once, and cheerful, even encouraging Nagi's butler [[Ayasaki Hayate]] to take up stand-up comedy and capitalize on his "hilariously woeful life".

title: sanzen'in_nagi
body:
Main female protagonist of [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

The spoiled, sheltered thirteen-year-old heiress to her family's vast fortune. She hires [[Ayasaki Hayate]] as butler after his attempt to kidnap her to escape the yakuza ended up sounding like a confession of love to her. Besides Hayate, she is also friends with her maid [[maria_(hayate_no_gotoku!)|Maria]], whom she treats as a mother figure.
Owing to her sheltered life (until recently), Nagi is somewhat socially inept, but also has an otaku-level obsession with anime, manga and video games, and is even writing her own doujin. Despite her intelligence (such that she skipped to first-year high school - the same grade as Hayate), Nagi is often too lazy to go to school.

title: ayasaki_hayate
body:
Main character of [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

A skilled but unlucky sixteen-year-old boy forced into paying off his irresponsible parents' huge debts. Escaping the yakuza, to whom he was sold by his parents, he tries to kidnap young heiress [[Sanzen'in Nagi]], only for his attempt to sound like a confession of love to the latter, and he subsequently ended up becoming her butler.
Besides his poverty, Hayate is also known for his effeminate looks, timidity and skill in "feminine" jobs like cooking, which sometimes ends him up being dressed by Nagi in girls' clothing.

title: hatsumoude
body: Hatsumoude (初詣) is the first [[shrine]] visit of the [[New Year]] in Japan. People visit a shrine or sometimes temple and [[praying|pray]] for comfort and health in the new year. It is very common to see women in [[kimono]] and quite a few men too. A common custom during hatsumōde is to buy a written oracle called [[omikuji]]. Also, new [[omamori|o-mamori]] (charms or amulets) are bought, and the old ones are returned to the shrine so they can be burned.

title: ten-tori_uranai
body:
[i]Ten-tori uranai[/i](点取占い) means "point-scoring fortune telling," and consists of folded strips of paper, similar to the [[omikuji]] found at Shinto shrines. They are sold in sets of 16 at "[i]dagashi-ya[/i]", old-fashioned Japanese sweet shops that sell low-priced snacks that children can easily afford.
On the strips of paper there is some writing and a mysterious symbol (one of 4 types, ○, ◐, ◑, ●) along with a number between 1 and 10. There is sometimes a clumsily-drawn picture, too. What characterizes this "toy" is what is written on the paper, which is very different from what you would expect from fortune-telling. It may be in the form of a question, (e.g., "Don't you care if I shout "You are stupid," at you?") an order, (e.g., "Scratch my itchy spot,") a statement (e.g., "You are a hopeless case,") a prohibition, (e.g., "Don't act like you know when you don't,") a wish, (e.g., "I want to play catch with a ghost,") a past tense sentence (e.g., "I felt dizzy at the top of Mount Fuji,") or something weird (e.g., "I've never heard my own sleeptalking,") and other such curious and mysterious sentences.

title: angelise_ikaruga_misurugi
body:
Angelise Ikaruga Misurugi, a.k.a Ange is the main protagonist of [i][[Cross Ange]][/i].

She is the beloved First Princess of the Empire of Misurugi. When it is discovered that she is a Norma, she is exiled to Arzenal and forced to shorten her name to "Ange". Being one of the soldiers of the Arzenal, her duty is to fight DRAGONs while piloting the Paramail named [[Villkiss (Cross Ange)|Villkiss]].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] and [[red eyes]]. [spoiler]She used to have [[long hair]] then, but decides to [[cutting hair|cut]] it short after her first sortie in the Villkiss.[/spoiler]

Voiced by [[Mizuki Nana]].

title: sunset_overdrive
body: Sunset Overdrive is an open world third-person shooter comedy video game developed by Insomniac Games and published by Microsoft Studios exclusively for the Xbox One. title: jill_valentine
body:
[b]Jill Valentine[/b] ([b]ジル・バレンタイン[/b]) is a Special Operations Agent (SOA) of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance, of which she is a co-founder and one of the original eleven members, making her a respected and high ranking operative of the organization. Prior to this, she was a member of S.T.A.R.S. Alpha team, Position RS (Rear Security). Before joining S.T.A.R.S., she was in the U.S. Army's Delta Force training program, where she earned extremely high grades in bomb disposal. She was brought into S.T.A.R.S. for her already well-developed fighting skills.

After joining up with S.T.A.R.S., she survived the infamous Mansion incident and the Raccoon City outbreak. She is the long time partner of [[Chris Redfield]], and as a result of their partnership, the two are engaged in a deep relationship, and Jill does really care about Chris' life when he is in danger, she would sacrifice her life for Chris, like she did in the Spencer's state. She has devoted almost her entire adult life to stopping bio-terrorism and hated enemy, [[Albert Wesker]].
